post_text:
Please note the 2 changes below to upcoming Board of Education Meetings:
1. July 28th Board Meeting has been moved to August 4th to finalize reopening plans.

2. A work session Board meeting is now scheduled for July 30th for the discussion of reopening school. The meeting will take place at 6:00 pm - no public will be permitted to attend; however, the meeting will stream live on Facebook.

A second parent survey will be released soon in regards to families' preferences for returning to school. We thank everyone for their patience and feedback during the planning process.

2. A work session Board meeting is now scheduled for July 30th for the discussion of reopening school. The meeting will take place at 6:00 pm - no public will be permitted to attend; however, the meeting will stream live on Facebook.

A second parent survey will be released soon in regards to families' preferences for returning to school. We thank everyone for their patience and feedback during the planning process.

We are getting excited to celebrate our seniors this weekend. The Class of 2020 will be recognized in a Virtual Graduation Ceremony on Star64 (Channel 12's sister station) on May 30th at 3:30-4:00 pm.

The Whitewater Crossing Mobile Food Pantry will be sharing food bags with any Three Rivers Families in need tomorrow (May 17, 2020) at CT Young (401 N. Miami Ave.) at 1:00 pm. The food bags will include peanut butter, cereal, hamburger patties, bread, canned fruit, vegetables, and other resources!
If your family requires a peanut-free bag, please let the distribution team know upon arrival.

Please know the team will also be following all CDC guidelines. Social distancing will be required; if recipients have masks/gloves, they are encouraged to wear them.

SENIOR PICTURE DAY:
On Wednesday, May 6th, we need all seniors to drive to school for us to take a professional picture in their cap and gown (times are in the link below). It is extremely important for all students to attend so that they are represented appropriately in our virtual ceremony.
